<U>
	Options
</U>
</DIV>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 100%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP">
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	Option holders do not have the right to receive dividends and are not entitled to vote at a meeting of the Company&#8217;s shareholders.&#160; Options may be exercised at any time from the date they vest to the date of their expiration.&#160; Share options convert into ordinary shares on a one for one basis on the date they are exercised.&#160;
</DIV>
</TD>
</TR>

	The share-based payment reserve is used to recognize the fair value of options and warrants issued to directors, executives, employees and consultants but not exercised.&#160; Amounts are transferred out of the reserve and into issued capital when the options or warrants are exercised.

<FONT STYLE="WIDTH: 12PT; DISPLAY: INLINE-BLOCK; FONT-SIZE: 1PX" ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;

	EXPENDITURE COMMITMENTS
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	The Company has non-cancelable operating leases contracted for but not capitalized in the financial statements.&#160; The Company has commitments under these contracts within one year of A$145,610 and greater than one year but less than three years of A$48,330.&#160; The property lease is a non-cancellable lease with an 18 month term, with rent payable monthly in advance.&#160; The property lease commenced April 1, 2015 and expires on September 30, 2017.&#160;
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	The majority of our contracts for research and development programs have a termination notice period of 30 days.&#160; As at June 30, 2016, we had research and development termination commitments approximating A$1.45 million.&#160; No liability has been recognized within our financial statements for this period.&#160; In addition, we have the ability to scale down our operations and prioritize our research and development programs in neurology to reduce expenditures.
</DIV>

</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: -14.2PT; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; MARGIN-LEFT: 14.2PT; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	(a)
<FONT STYLE="WIDTH: 12PT; DISPLAY: INLINE-BLOCK; FONT-SIZE: 1PX" ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;
</FONT>
	Employee and Consultant Plans
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	At the Annual General Meeting held on
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	November 17, 2004
</FONT>
	, the shareholders approved the establishment of employee and consultant plans designed to reward directors, employees and consultants for their contributions to the Company.&#160; The plans are to be used as a method of retaining key personnel for the growth and development of the Company.&#160; Due to Prana&#8217;s U.S. presence, a U.S. plan (the 2004 ADS Plan) and an Australian plan (the 2004 ASX Plan) were developed.&#160;
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	At 30 June 2016 equity had been issued to 1 previous Director, while a Director, under the US plan and 6 Directors, 2 Key Management Personnel, 12 employees and 19 consultants under the Australian Plan. At June 30, 2015, equity had been issued to one former Director under the 2004 ADS Plan and six Directors, three key management personnel, 16 employees and 19 consultants under the 2004 ASX Plan.&#160; At June 30, 2014, equity had been issued to one former Director under the 2004 ADS Plan and six Directors, three key management personnel, 16 employees and 19 consultants under the 2004 ASX Plan.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	At the 2004 Annual General Meeting, shareholders authorized the Company to issue in the aggregate up to 12 million ordinary shares under the two plans.&#160; This was increased to 22 million ordinary shares at the 2005 Annual General Meeting and further increased to 30 million ordinary shares at the 2007 Annual General Meeting, 45 million ordinary shares at the 2008 Annual General Meeting and 60 million ordinary shares at the 2009 Annual General Meeting.&#160; The Share Plan Committee, a sub-committee of the Remuneration Committee administers the two plans and is able to change the terms of the equity issued under them from the default terms
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	Under the 2004 ADS Plan, the exercise price must equal or exceed the fair value of the ADS on the date the options are awarded.&#160; The option expiration date cannot exceed ten years from the date the options were awarded.&#160; The default vesting conditions are 25% per year on the date the options were awarded.&#160;
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	Under the 2004 ASX Plan, the exercise price must be equal or be less than the market value of the ordinary shares on ASX on the date of grant.&#160; The option expiration date cannot exceed ten years from the date the options were granted.&#160; The default vesting conditions are 25% per year on the date the options were granted.&#160;
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	Information with respect to the number of options granted under the 2004 ASX Plan as follows:
</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; CLEAR: BOTH">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE: ITALIC; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	Risk free interest rate
</FONT>
	&#8211; This is the government bond rate (having a term that most closely resembles the expected life of the option) in effect at the grant date.&#160; The Australian government bond rate has been used for options which are exercisable for fully paid ordinary shares and the U.S. government bond rate has been used for options which are exercisable for ADRs.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE: ITALIC; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	Dividend yield
</FONT>
	&#8211; Prana has never declared or paid dividends on its ordinary shares and does not anticipate paying any dividends in the foreseeable future.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE: ITALIC; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	Expected volatility
</FONT>
	&#8211; Prana estimates expected volatility based on historical volatility over the estimated life of the option and other factors.&#160; Historical volatility has been the basis for determining expected share price volatility as it is assumed that this is indicative of future movements.&#160; The life of the options is based on historical exercise patterns, which may not eventuate in the future.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE: ITALIC; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	Expected life
</FONT>
	&#8211; This is the period of time that the options granted are expected to remain outstanding. This estimate is based primarily on historical trend of option holders to exercise their option near the date of expiry.&#160; As a result the expected life is considered to equal the period from grant date to expiry date.&#160;
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">

	PricewaterhouseCoopers was appointed as the Company&#8217;s principal independent registered public accounting firm on November 30, 2006.&#160; Australian law does not require the Company&#8217;s Auditors to be appointed at the Company&#8217;s annual general meeting of shareholders.&#160; There is an annual engagement letter which is signed, subject to the Company&#8217;s audit committee approval, with PricewaterhouseCoopers for audit and review work.&#160; No non-audit services were provided by PricewaterhouseCoopers during the
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	2016,
</FONT>
	2015
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	and 2014
</FONT>
	fiscal years.&#160;

	Chief Financial Officer
</DIV>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	Remuneration of all key management personnel of the Company is determined by the Board of Directors following recommendation by the Remuneration Committee.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	The Company is committed to remunerating senior executives in a manner that is market competitive and consistent with &#8216;best practice&#8217; including the interests of shareholders.&#160; Remuneration packages are based on fixed and variable components, determined by the executive&#8217;s position, experience and performance, and may be satisfied via cash or equity.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	Non-executive Directors are remunerated out of the aggregate amount approved by shareholders and at a level that is consistent with industry standards.&#160; Non-executive Directors do not receive performance based bonuses and prior shareholder approval is required to participate in any issuance of equity.&#160; No retirement benefits are payable other than statutory superannuation, if applicable.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	The Company's remuneration policy is not solely based on the Company's performance, but also on industry practice.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	The Company's primary focus is research activities with a long term objective of developing and commercializing its research and development results.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	The Company envisages its performance in terms of earnings will remain negative whilst the Company continues in the research and clinical trials.&#160; Shareholder wealth reflects this speculative and volatile market sector.&#160; This pattern is indicative of the Company's performance over the past four years.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	The purpose of a performance bonus is to reward individual performance in line with Company objectives.&#160; Consequently, performance based remuneration is paid to an individual where the individual's performance clearly contributes to a successful outcome for the Company.&#160; This is regularly measured in respect of performance against key performance indicators ("KPI's").
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	The Company uses a variety of KPI's to determine achievement, depending on the role of the executive being assessed.&#160; These include:
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY: SYMBOL, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&#183;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="WIDTH: 28.2PT; DISPLAY: INLINE-BLOCK; FONT-SIZE: 1PX" ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	successful contract negotiations;
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY: SYMBOL, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&#183;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="WIDTH: 28.2PT; DISPLAY: INLINE-BLOCK; FONT-SIZE: 1PX" ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	Company share price reaching a targeted rate on the ASX or applicable market over a period of time; or
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY: SYMBOL, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&#183;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="WIDTH: 28.2PT; DISPLAY: INLINE-BLOCK; FONT-SIZE: 1PX" ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	achievement of research project milestones within scheduled time and/or budget.&#160;
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD" ID="DSPFPAGEFOOTER">
	PRANA BIOTECHNOLOGY LIMITED
</DIV>
<DIV ID="DSPFPAGEHEADER">
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: -14.2PT; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; MARGIN-LEFT: 14.2PT; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	NOTES TO CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS &#8211; in Australian dollars (unless otherwise noted)
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	23.
<FONT STYLE="WIDTH: 12PT; DISPLAY: INLINE-BLOCK; FONT-SIZE: 1PX" ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;
</FONT>
	SEGMENT INFORMATION
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	The Company&#8217;s Chief Executive Officer (Chief Operating Decision Maker) examines internal reports to assess the Company&#8217;s performance and determine the allocation of resources.&#160; The Company&#8217;s activities are predominantly within Australia and cover research into Alzheimer&#8217;s
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	disease
</FONT>
	, Huntington
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	disease
</FONT>
	, Parkinson&#8217;s
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	disease
</FONT>
	and other neurodegenerative disorders.&#160; Accordingly, the Company has identified one reportable segment.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	24.
<FONT STYLE="WIDTH: 12PT; DISPLAY: INLINE-BLOCK; FONT-SIZE: 1PX" ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;
</FONT>
	FINANCIAL INSTRUMENTS
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	The Company&#8217;s activities expose it to a variety of financial risks including market risk, credit risk and liquidity risk. The Company&#8217;s overall risk management program focuses on the unpredictability of financial markets and seeks to minimize potential adverse effects on the financial performance of the Company. Risk management is carried out under policies approved by the Board of Directors and overseen by the Audit, Risk and Compliance Committee.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: -36PT; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; MARGIN-LEFT: 36PT; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	(a)
<FONT STYLE="WIDTH: 12PT; DISPLAY: INLINE-BLOCK; FONT-SIZE: 1PX" ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;
</FONT>
	Market Risk
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	(i)&#160; Foreign Currency Risk
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	The Company engages in international purchase transactions and is exposed to foreign currency risk arising from various currency exposures, primarily with respect to the Australian dollar. The parent entity also has exposure to foreign exchange risk in the currency cash reserves it holds to meet its foreign currency payments. The Company does not make use of derivative financial instruments to hedge foreign exchange risk.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; CLEAR: BOTH">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	The Company has conducted a sensitivity analysis of its exposure to foreign currency risk. The Company is currently exposed to the US dollar (USD), Euro (EUR) and British Pound (GBP). The sensitivity analysis below is conducted on a currency by currency basis using the sensitivity analysis variable, which has been based on the average annual movement in the AUD/USD, AUD/GBP and AUD/EUR exchange rates over the past 5 years based on the year-end spot rates.&#160; The variables for USD, GBP and EUR being 3%, 12% and 3% respectively.&#160; All the amounts in the table below are displayed in Australian Dollars (A$).
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	Based on the financial instruments held at June 30, 2016, had the Australian dollar weakened/strengthened by 3% against the US dollar, 12% against the GBP and 3% against the EURO with all other variables held constant, the Company's post-tax loss for the year would have been A$634,419 lower/A$673,431 higher (2015: A$786,576 lower/A$835,247 higher), mainly as a result of foreign exchange gains/losses on translation of US dollar denominated financial instruments as detailed in the above table.&#160; The Company&#8217;s exposure to other foreign exchange movements is not material.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
	&#160;
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	We realized a foreign exchange gain of A$950,720 for the year ended June 30, 2016 compared to a foreign exchange loss of A$4,953,253 for the year ended June 30, 2015 and a foreign exchange gain of A$581,263 for the year ended June 30, 2014. In 2016, the Australian dollar depreciated against the U.S. dollar by 3%.&#160; In 2015, the Australian dollar depreciated against the U.S. dollar by 18%, while in 2014, the Australian dollar appreciated against the U.S. dollar by 3%.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
	&#160;
</DIV>

<A NAME="eolPage122"></A>

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
	&#160;
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD" ID="DSPFPAGEFOOTER">
	PRANA BIOTECHNOLOGY LIMITED
</DIV>
<DIV ID="DSPFPAGEHEADER">
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: -14.2PT; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; MARGIN-LEFT: 14.2PT; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	NOTES TO CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS &#8211; in Australian dollars (unless otherwise noted)
</DIV>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
	&#160;
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	24.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="WIDTH: 29.2PT; DISPLAY: INLINE-BLOCK; FONT-SIZE: 1PX" ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	FINANCIAL INSTRUMENTS (continued)
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: -14.2PT; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; MARGIN-LEFT: 14.2PT; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	(b)
<FONT STYLE="WIDTH: 12PT; DISPLAY: INLINE-BLOCK; FONT-SIZE: 1PX" ID="TRGRRTFTOHTMLTAB">
	&#160;
</FONT>
	Credit Risk
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	Credit risk refers to the risk that a counterparty will default on its contractual obligations resulting in financial loss to the Company.&#160; The Company has no significant concentration of credit risk and it is not the Company&#8217;s policy to hedge credit risk.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	The Company ensures that surplus cash is invested with financial institutions of appropriate credit worthiness and limits the amount of credit exposure to any one counter party.&#160;
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	There has been no significant change in the Company&#8217;s exposure to credit risk since the previous year.&#160; The carrying amount of the Company&#8217;s financial assets
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	represents
</FONT>
	the maximum credit exposure.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	(c) Liquidity Risk
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	Prudent liquidity risk management implies maintaining sufficient cash and the availability of funding through an adequate amount of committed credit facilities.&#160; The Company manages liquidity risk by maintaining sufficient bank balances to fund its operations and the availability of funding through committed credit facilities.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	Management monitors rolling forecasts of the Company&#8217;s liquidity reserve on the basis of expected cash flows.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; CLEAR: BOTH; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	&#160;
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	(d) Capital Risk Management
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	The Company's objectives when managing capital are to safeguard the Company's ability to continue as a going concern and to maintain an optimal capital structure so as to maximize shareholder value.&#160; In order to maintain or achieve an optimal capital structure, the Company may issue new shares or reduce its capital, subject to the provisions of the Company's constitution. The capital structure of the Company consists of equity attributed to equity holders of the Company, comprising contributed equity, reserves and accumulated losses disclosed in
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	Notes 12, 13 and 14
</FONT>
	.&#160; By monitoring undiscounted cash flow forecasts and actual cash flows provided to the Board by the Company's Management the Board monitors the need to raise additional equity from the equity markets.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	(e) Fair Value Estimation
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	The carrying amount of financial assets and financial liabilities recorded in the financial statements represents their respective fair values, determined in accordance with the accounting policies disclosed in Note 1 to the financial statements.
</DIV>

<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	Financial Instruments measured at Fair Value
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	The financial instruments recognized at fair value in the Statement of Financial Position have been analyzed and classified using a fair value hierarchy reflecting the significance of the inputs used in making the measurements. The fair value hierarchy consists of the following levels:
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&#160;
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH: 100%; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT" ID="Z9B1B941DEF1C40DAA54D153A69BB2E2C" CLASS="DSPFLISTTABLE" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 14.2PT; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP; ALIGN: RIGHT">
	-
</TD>
<TD STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; WIDTH: AUTO; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP">
	quoted prices in active markets for identical assets or liabilities (Level 1);
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH: 100%; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT" ID="Z3E02336EE0DA4FA6B545D53FE5FA6409" CLASS="DSPFLISTTABLE" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 14.2PT; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP; ALIGN: RIGHT">
	-
</TD>
<TD STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; WIDTH: AUTO; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP">
	inputs other than quoted prices included within Level 1 that are observable for the asset or liability, either directly (as prices) or indirectly (derived from prices) (Level 2); and
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH: 100%; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT" ID="ZAD66DB051FA748A09D5DC3268F741A1F" CLASS="DSPFLISTTABLE" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 14.2PT; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP; ALIGN: RIGHT">
	-
</TD>
<TD STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; WIDTH: AUTO; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP">
	inputs for the asset or liability that are not based on observable market data (unobservable inputs) (Level 3).
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<BR STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	In 2016 and 2015, none of the Company&#8217;s assets and liabilities except for the other financial liabilities had their fair value determined using the fair value hierarchy.&#160; The other financial liabilities are classified as level 2 instruments. No transfers between the levels of the fair value hierarchy occurred during the current or previous years.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: -18PT; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; MARGIN-LEFT: 18PT; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	&#160;
</DIV>

	25.

<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH: 100%; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT" ID="Z4C0364F2681044DCB89A8AEB0D253D83" CLASS="DSPFLISTTABLE" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0">

	Prana has sought the assistance of IDT to formulate, develop and manufacture API and finished dosage forms, analytical testing (including stability and microbiological testing), clinical packaging and distribution of clinical trial materials for Prana&#8217;s proprietary product/s such as PBT434 and PBT2 and matching placebo for clinical trials.&#160; There may also be occasions in future where Prana may call on IDT to provide other pharmaceutical manufacturing and related services.
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
	&#160;
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; MARGIN-LEFT: 35.45PT; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE: ITALIC; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	Force Majeure
</FONT>
	means an act of God, strike, lock-out or other labour dispute, war declared or undeclared, blockade, riot, insurrection, lightning, fire, earthquake, storm, flood, explosion, restraint of government or government agency, prohibition or any other cause whether or not of the kind listed above which is beyond the control of the party affected.
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
	&#160;
</DIV>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

</FONT>

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
	&#160;

<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH: 100%; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT" ID="ZDB404A4FB3E44FC3824CD435E398997E" CLASS="DSPFLISTTABLE" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 35.45PT">
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 35.45PT; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP; ALIGN: RIGHT">
	12.3
</TD>
<TD STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; WIDTH: AUTO; FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP">
	Upon the termination of this Agreement or any Work Order pursuant to clauses 12.1, 12.2 or 13.2, IDT may invoice Prana for Services and reimbursable expenses and non-cancellable commitments properly performed or incurred in accordance with this Agreement and the applicable Work Order through to the date of termination (
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY: 'TIMES NEW ROMAN', TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
	Final Invoice
</FONT>
	). In the absence of any offsetting claim, Prana agrees to immediately pay all outstanding invoices and otherwise pay the Final Invoice (or so much thereof as may be due having regard to any up-front fees already paid) within 30 days of the date of the invoice. If after raising the Final Invoice, Prana&#8217;s account is in credit, then IDT shall immediately refund the credit balance.
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

	If any party to this Agreement is unable to carry out any obligation (other than to pay money), by reason of Force Majeure, then that obligation will be suspended so far as it is affected by the Force Majeure for the duration of the Force Majeure.&#160; The party affected must promptly give written notice to the other party of the Force Majeure with full particulars thereof and so far as is known, the probable extent to which that party will be unable to perform or will be delayed in performing the obligation.

	Without limiting any other means by which a party may be able to prove that a notice has been received by the other party, a notice will be considered to have been received:
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
	&#160;
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">

	The rights, remedies and powers of the parties under this Agreement are cumulative and do not exclude any other rights, remedies or powers.

	Once executed by both parties, this Work Order will be incorporated into the MSA. Capitalized terms not defined in this Work Order shall have the meanings ascribed to them in the MSA.

	Designed such internal control over financial reporting, or caused such internal control over financial reporting to be designed under our supervision, to provide reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of financial reporting and the preparation of financial statements for external purposes in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles;

</FONT>

	&#160;
